  "text": "The audit logging for authorization decisions in Apache Kafka is implemented in the StandardAuthorizerData class located at metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizerData.java. This class is responsible for evaluating ACL-based authorization decisions and logging them for compliance and audit purposes.\n\nKey audit logging mechanisms:\n\n1. **Main Audit Logger**: The class uses a dedicated logger named 'kafka.authorizer.logger' obtained through LoggerFactory.getLogger(\"kafka.authorizer.logger\") (line 116).\n\n2. **Authorization Decision Logging**: The authorize() method (lines 228-252) processes authorization decisions for actions. For each action, it calls logAuditMessage() (line 250) to record the decision.\n\n3. **ALLOWED Events**: When an authorization is ALLOWED (lines 288-297), the class logs at debug level if logIfAllowed flag is true (line 292-293), otherwise at trace level (line 295). The log message includes the principal, operation, resource type, host, request type, and matching rule.\n\n4. **DENIED Events**: When an authorization is DENIED (lines 299-308), the class logs at info level if logIfDenied flag is true (line 305), otherwise at trace level (line 307). DENIED events are logged more prominently as they represent security-relevant decisions.\n\n5. **Audit Message Format**: The buildAuditMessage() method (lines 254-271) constructs detailed audit log entries that include:\n   - Principal (user/client making the request)\n   - Authorization decision (Allowed or Denied)\n   - Operation being performed\n   - Source host IP address\n   - Resource being accessed (resource type, pattern type, resource name)\n   - Request API name\n   - Resource reference count (for metrics tracking)\n   - Matching ACL rule information\n\n6. **ACL-Based Authorization**: The class evaluates whether an ACL matches the request through the findAclRule() method (lines 312-366), checking principal, host, operation, and resource pattern matching. The result determines if the action is ALLOWED or DENIED based on ACL definitions.\n\nThe StandardAuthorizerData class is used by StandardAuthorizer (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizer.java), which is the built-in authorizer implementation for KRaft-based Kafka clusters. This provides comprehensive audit trail functionality for all authorization decisions made by the Kafka cluster."
}

